         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">23/5/93. ¶  ¶ This time, noble friend, I am just writing to ascertain whether the  ¶ alpine lichens ¶  (from Mt Erika ¶ ) that I sent you at the beginning of this year have proved to be remarkable. I ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">93.05.23</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Jean Müller</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Conservatoire et Jardin botanique, Geneva.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">23/5/93.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Diesmal, edler Freund, schreibe ich nur, um zu erfahren, ob die <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Alpen-Flechten</hi>
               </seg> (von Mt Erika) welche ich im Beginn dieses Jahres an Sie absandte sich als merkwürdig erwiesen haben. Ich veranlasste meine beiden Assistenten diesen (5 Monate im Jahr mit Schnee begipfelten) Berg zu ersteigen, voraus sehend, dass sich keine neue Vascular Pflanzen zeigen würden, so dass sich das Interesse an die Evasculares knüpft.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich denke, Sie werden mir freundlichst ausschreiben, wie <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Sie</hi>
               </seg> die <name key="Monochlamydeae">Monochlamydeae</name> vertheilen würden. Ich habe die <name key="Sarraceniaceae">Sarraceniaceae</name> neben <name key="Saxifrageae">Saxifrageae</name>
               <name key="Nepenthaceae">Nepenthaceae</name> und <name key="Droseraceae">Droseraceae</name> gestellt. Der Same von Darlington. selbst bis zu seinem grossen Embryo ist ganz wie bei <name key="Nepenthes">Nepenthes</name>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich werde Ihnen den Druck meiner Rede senden, die ich zum Andenken an Alph. D.C. vor unserem Feld-Naturalisten Club gab vor 2 Wochen als dessen Patron. Ein rührender letzter Brief von dem grossen Todten kam an mich, dadirt von <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">mitte</hi>
               </seg> März, nach fast 40 jähriger Correspondenz.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Sie ehrend der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Ich stelle jetzt die <name key="Stackhousiaceae">Stackhousiaceae</name> (minus <name key="Macgregoria">Macgregoria</name>, die nahe den Geraniaceen (<name key="Floerkea%20">Floerkea </name>nach Baillon) steht nahe <name key="Halorageae">Halorageae</name>.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">23/5/93.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This time, noble friend, I am just writing to ascertain whether the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">alpine lichens</hi>
               </seg> (from Mt Erika<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Mt Erica, Vic.</p>
               </note>) that I sent you at the beginning of this year have proved to be remarkable. I arranged for both my assistants to climb this mountain (topped with snow five months of the year), foreseeing that no new vascular plants would show up so that the interest is connected to the evasculars.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am thinking you will kindly write out for me how <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">you</hi>
               </seg> would divide the <name key="Monochlamydeae">Monochlamydeae</name>. I have put the <name key="Sarraceniaceae">Sarraceniaceae</name> together with <name key="Saxifrageae">Saxifrageae</name>, <name key="Nepenthaceae">Nepenthaceae</name> and <name key="Droseraceae">Droseraceae</name>. The seed of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Darlington.</seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <name key="Darlingtonia">Darlingtonia</name>.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg> even down to its large embryo, is quite like that in <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Nepenthes">Nepenthes</name>
               </seg>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will send you the printing of my speech that I gave at the commemoration of Alphonse de Candolle before our Field Naturalists' Club two weeks ago as its patron.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B93.06.04. Candolle died on 4 April 1893.</p>
               </note> A touching last letter from the great deceased came to me, dated from the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">middle</hi>
               </seg> of March,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See A. de Candolle to M, 17 March 1893.</p>
               </note> after almost 40 years of correspondence.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Respectfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I now place the <name key="Stackhousiaceae">Stackhousiaceae</name> (minus <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Macgregoria">Macgregoria</name>
               </seg>, which stands near the <name key="Geraniaceae">Geraniaceae</name> (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Floerkea</seg> according to Baillon) near <name key="Halorageae">Halorageae</name>.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M was thinking about a planned third edition of his Systematic census of Australian plants, and the systematic arrangement he would use in it. The edition was never completed. See M to J. Müller, 18 April 1893, and notes thereto.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
